verbose_text: In agreement with these studies, high PL content in HDL2 particles has been found to be an efficient driving factor for cholesterol removal from peripheral cells [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR], an intravenous infusion of apo AI/PC discs to stimulate reverse cholesterol transport in humans [XREF_BIBR], and plasma HDL-PL levels to inversely correlate to the extent of atherosclerosis in coronary arteries [XREF_BIBR].
